 \text{Let} \cos^{-1}0.8 = \theta\\ \cos \theta = 0.8 \\ 1-2\sin^2\frac{\theta}{2} = 0.8 \\ \sin^2\frac{\theta}{2} = 0.1 \\ \sin\frac{\theta}{2} = \sqrt{0.1} \space \text{(think about why it is not negative)} \\ \sin\left(\frac{1}{2}\cos^{-1}0.8\right) = \sqrt{0.1} 
